This repository contains a derivative of the autoware_diffusion_planner ROS 2
package from the Autoware Universe project:

    https://github.com/autowarefoundation/autoware_universe
    Copyright (c) 2025 TIER IV, Inc.
    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Our modifications add:
  - Split-ONNX inference (context encoder + DiT core + turn-indicator head)
  - Native C++ implementation of DPM-Solver++ (orders 1, 2) and DDIM
  - Encoder caching across denoising steps
  - Per-step trajectory observability for analysis
  - Runtime-configurable solver type and step count

A full diff against upstream Autoware Universe is provided in
patches/modular_planner_vs_upstream.patch.

The diffusion planner architecture is based on:

    Zheng, Y., Wang, R., Yan, Y., Hu, X., Wang, S., Tomizuka, M., Zhan, W.
    "Diffusion-Based Planning for Autonomous Driving with Flexible Guidance"
    arXiv:2501.15564, 2025.
    Original implementation: https://github.com/ZhengYinan-AIR/Diffusion-Planner
